    "body": "In Prater genesis after drifting the clock a lot and recovering the node throws `ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE` for all late arriving attestations.\r\n\r\n```\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:53 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:53 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:53 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:53 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n2021-03-23 15:18:53 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n\r\n... 768 times total ...\r\n\r\n2021-03-23 15:19:18 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n2021-03-23 15:19:18 [NETWORK]         debug: gossip - AggregateAndProof - ignore code=ATTESTATION_ERROR_MISSING_ATTESTATION_PRESTATE\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Does libp2p cache the messages somewhere? How are the old attestations arriving now instead of the new ones?\r\n- Can the attestation pre-state status be cached so it's not re-tried and failed 768 times?",
